messages.message: Can you tell me about Vojvodina?
Vojvodinoa is one of two provinces in Serbia.
hm interesting, Can you tell me about their economy?
Vojvodina promotes its investment potentials through the Vojvodina investment promotion.
Can you tell me anything else about their economy?
Vijvodina uses the International and cross-border economic cooperation as well as to implement priorities defined within the strategy for the Danube region.
Can you tell me about their Demographics?
Slovaks are the largest ethnic group in Vojvodina.
Can you tell me anything else?
They constitute a majority in Backyl Petrovac and they also constitute the largest percent of the population.
Can you give me a fun fact?
Its capital and largest city is Novi Sad.
Hello! Can you please tell me something about Bihar please?
I sure can. Bihar is a state in the Republic of India. It covers an area of 38,202 square miles.
Oh okay! What about some history about Bihar?
Until 1912, Bihar remained a part of the Bengal Presidency of British India . Then the province of Bihar and Orissa was carved out as a separate province.
Oh okay! How about their demographics in Bihar?
Bihar as the second lowest urbanization rate in India. The urbanization rate of Bihar is at 11.3%.
Alright! Can you tell me something about their culture?

Unfortunately, I do not have any information about the culture. To follow up with more demographics, I can share with you that 58% of Bihar's population is below the age of 25. This is the highest rate in India.
Ohh wow! What about some information about their cuisine?
Sorry, I do not have any information about the cuisine in Bihar. Again, I can share some additional facts on the demographics. 82.7% of Bihar's population practices Hinduism.
Okay! What about some fun facts about Bihar.
Bihar is the 4th -argest producer of vegetables and the 8th-largest producer of fruits in India.
Okay! Thank you for your help. Have a nice evening. Bye for now.
Goodbye, you are welcome.
Hello I need help in gathering information about United Arab Emirates.
Sure. The United Arab Emirates is also known as the UAE. It is a country in the Middle East, being made up of seven emirates located in the Arabian Peninsula. What else can I tell you about?
I need information about their Telecommunications.
There are two telecommunications operators that serve the UAE; Etisilat and Emirates Integrated.
Do you have more information about Etisalat?

Etisalat operated under a monopoly until mobile services were launched in 2007. The Telecommunications Regulatory Authority mandates the filtering of websites for political, religious, and sexual content.
Aww interesting, thank you for that info., Do you have information about their education?
In public schools, the medium of instruction is Arabic, while English is emphasized as a second language.
What type of education system do they use?
The UAE's ministry is responsible for the admission of students to its undergraduate institutions, the American University of Sharjah, and the University of Sharjah.
Nice, that all I need to know. Thank you for the informations.
You're welcome
Can you teach me about Equador?
It is a small country in South America.Spain was interested in finding gold in Ecuador so it was part of the Spanish Empire.
Oh interesting. What can you tell me about the culture?
Football is the most popular sport in Ecuador as is with most South American countries.
Is it actual football or more like soccer?
It is soccer to most Americans but they call it football. The most successful team is LDU Quito they were runners up in the 2008 FIFA club world cup.
Oh good for them. That's enough about culture. Can you tell me about their economy?
Sorry nothing about the economy at the moment.
Hmm, okay. Is there anything else you can tell me about culture then?
Ecuador's Amerindian communities integrate with mainstream culture to some degree. Some practice their own native culture particularly the more remote Amerindian communities of thr Amazon basin.
Okay, thanks so much. You've been a really big help. I just wished to learn more about the economy.
Sorry about that have a good day.
Hello there, may I please get some facts on Northern Territory?
Sure the Northern Territory is located in Australia.
Thank you for that, do you have any historical facts?
Yes it was part of South Australia from 1863 to 1911.
Oh wow, I never knew that!
It also represent 1 percent of Australia's population it is the most sparsely populated.
Do you have access to any facts on the economy?
It's economy is characterized by its Natural Resources
What are some of the natural resources?
Unfortunately specifics are not available.
No worries, Thank you for all of your help.
You are welcome
What can you tell me about Syrian demographics?
Hi! Brazil is the first country in the Americas to offer humanitarian visas to Syrian refugees.
Oh? What are the statistics of Syrian refugees in Brazil today?

The exact number in Brazil isn't gen but it is millions but 9.5 million Syrians have been displaced since the Syrian Civil War in 2011. 4.9 million had fled to neighboring countries like Turkey, Jordan, Iraq, and Lebanon.
Wow nice Any fact on how the Syrian presence affected the economy?
The majority of Syrian cargo is carried by Syrian Railways which links up with Turkish State Railways.
Thanks. Now how about the eduction in Syria?
No details on education as of yet but the national capital of Syria is Damascus.
There aren't any reform efforts regarding education? That's unfortunate. Can you tell me about culture?

I agree. As for the culture, Syria was once home to to substantial population of Jews with large Jewish communities in Damascus, Aleppo (the biggest city in Syria), and Qamishii. 75% of Syrian population is Sunni, 12% Alawi, 10% Christian, and 3% Druze.
Thanks for this information. Any last fact?
You are welcome. There's also many popular football teams in Syria which are based in Damascus, Aleppo, Homs, and Latakia.
Interesting. Are there any sports competitions?

I couldn't find any details on that but I finally got a bit of information here about education in Syria. The top 2 state universities are Damascus University and University of Aleppo. The top ranking universities in the country are Damascus University (ranked 3540th worldwide) and Tishreen University (ranked 7968th worldwide) according to Webometrics Ranking of World Universities.
Thank you for answering my questions!
My pleasure!
Good evening. I was hoping you could help me learn about Turkey.
Hello, Turkey is a country in Europe but at the same time in Asia. Turkey is a republic which has 81 provinces. Its capital is Ankara.
That is interesting that it is in both Europe and Asia. Can you tell a little more about Turkey's Geography?
The Asian turkey includes 97 % of the country and it is separated from the European Turkey by the Bosphorous, sea of Marmara, and the Dardanelles.
So they are considered to separate entities?

Unfortunately, I do not have this information at that moment but I can tell you that the Asian part of the country is comprised by the peninsula of Anatolia between the Koroglu and Pontiac mountains ranges to the north and the Taurus Mountains to the South
It must be so beautiful with all those mountains. Do you have any information you can share with me about the etymology of Turkey?
No I do not have information about Etymology of Turkey but I can tell you that its name means "Land of Turks"
Can you tell me what language or languages they speak there? I wonder if it is different for the Europe side and the Asian side.
Official language is Turkey with the 85 % of people.11% speak Kurmanshi and the rest Arabic or Zaza
Interesting. That's a variety. Thank you so much for your help. I hope you have a good rest of your night.
you welcome!
Can you tell me about Western Sahara?

Western Sahara is a territory in Africa. to the North is Morocco, to the East is Algeria, to the South is Mauritania, and to the West is the Atlantic ocean. It is one of the most sparsely populated territories in the world. Most of the territory is made of desert of flatlands. The largest city is Laayoune. More than half the population lived there the territory has a population estimated at just more than 500000 Western Sahara has been on the United Nations list of non self governing territory since the 1960s when it was a Spanish colony. The Kingdom of Morocco and the polisario front independence movement with its Sahrawri Arab democratic Republic government both won control of the territory.
Interesting! What can you tell me about the History?

After an agreement among the European colonial powers at the Berlin conference in 1884 and the division of spheres of influence in Africa, Spain seized control of the Western Sahara and established it as a Spanish colony.
Do you have any other interesting facts about the History?

During the annual celebration of Muhammad's birthday these lords paid their respects to the caliph to show loyalty to the Moroccan monarchy. As time went by, Spanish colonial rule began to unravel with the general wave of decolonization after World War II. Former North African and sub saharan African possessions and protectorates gained independence from European powers.
Interesting! What can you tell me about the Politics?

I don't have any information on politics at the moment. I can tell you about the geography. Western Sahara is located on the Northwest coast in West africa and on the cusp of North Africa bordering the north Atlantic ocean to the north West Morocco proper to the north North East Algeria to the east North East and Mauritania to the east and South.
Can you tell me anything about the economy?

Unfortunately, I have no info on that either. I can tell you about culture though. Local religious custom is like other sohar and groups heavily influenced by pre Islamic Berber and African practices and differ substantially from urban practices.
Can you tell me any fun facts?
Am interesting fact is that most of the food for the urban population comes from Moocco.
Thank you! The information has been great!
It's been my pleasure!

messages.message: Hi! Good evening. Can you tell me about Armenia?
Armenia is a country bordered by Turkey and Georgia in Eastern Europe.
Thank you, can you tell me more about Armenia's History?
Their history dates the entire way back to 860 BC. In 428 The Kingdom of Armenia fell to the Sasanian Empire. During the 1230'2 Armenia was part of the Mongol Empire.
Wow! I didn't know that. Very interesting. Can you tell me anymore about their history?
In 1045 the Byzantine Empire conquered the area and in the 16th century it was part of the Safavid Empire.
Great info! I'd also like to learn more about their government and politics. Can you help me with that?

Currently the government supports Armenian schools even those outside of Armenia. The schools were rebuilt in the country by the government. They also offer $700000 to any athletes that win a gold medal at the Olympics.
Tjat

Wrestling has been one of the most successful Olympic sports for Armenia. And when they were part of the USSR, Armenian helped them win lots of medals in various sports. Russia is still allies with Armenia and they even have a military base in it's borders as a deterrent to Turkey.

My apologies for the previous message. Finger got a little jumpy. That's so cool they offer that to Olympic hopefuls! They really seem invested in Olympic glory. Do you have anymore fun facts to share?
One of the oldest types of Armenian music is the Armenian chant which is a common type of religious music.
Wonder if I can find that one on Spotify. Thank you so much for all of your help! You've really given me a lot of great information.
YOu are welcome!
I want to learn about Kenya!

Okay! Kenya is country in East Africa, about half way down, near the horn of Africa. It has the Indian Ocean to its east and Lake Victoria to to its west. Kenya borders the nations of Somalia, Ethiopia, South Sudan, Uganda, and Tanzania.
That is great! What about their Economy?
In March 1996, the presidents of Kenya, Tanzania, and Uganda reestablished the East African Community, or the EAC.
What else can you tell me?
In 2016 Kenya rose from the 113rd to the 92nd place in ease of doing business. It has an estimated economic growth of over 5% since 2012.
What about their demographics?
There is an estimated 38.6 million people living there and British English is the primary language there as they were a British colony to start but gained its independence in December of 1963.
Thank you so much for all that information.
You're most welcome!
Have a great evening.
You too!
